Antennae (
Fig. 14
) slender, 0.57 times as long as body, length ratio of antennomeres I–XI equal to 100: 71: 100: 114: 157: 143: 143: 143: 129: 129: 186.

Pronotum (
Fig. 9
) as wide as long, widest in middle. Surface weakly constricted before base, constriction densely covered with fine punctures. Anterior margin nearly straight, thinly bordered, lateral margins distinctly rounded, anterior half of lateral margins moderately convergent anteriorly, posterior half convergently rounded to basal constriction.
